children.subject: I don't think that they're going to change any scheduling of popular classes, but dual enrollment for conflicting classes is a thing. Plus, CS170 tends to have webcasted lectures (can't speak on 120), so you can still attend 120 lectures live if you prefer that. If the schedule conflict is a problem for you, consider this dual enrollment as an alternative.

history.content: 170 will not be moved.  Our original intention was to schedule it at a different time but no lecture halls were available on campus at our preferred time. (That was true for 7 (!) of our UG classes and so the schedule is sub-optimal and yet we are able to offer the classes which was up in the air for a bit.

CS170 and EE120 are basically the gateway classes for CS theory and signal processing, so it is common to take them together after finishing lower divs. However, the are scheduled for the same time block this year.

Is it possible that the schedule can change in the future?
history.subject: Is it possible that the time for EE120 or CS170 be moved?
